    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-03T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-03T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 3, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 3—7:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>863. Legation’s 862, November 3, 3 p.m. The Consul General at Mukden on November
                    2, 5 p.m., reported the closing by Japanese of the Chinese electric light plant
                    at Changchun; the Japanese plant is supplying current. He is reliably informed
                    that the Japanese are installing a transformer leading to the old Chinese plant
                    in Mukden, intending to close this and to furnish current from Fushun. These two
                    cases, along with that at Antung, appear to indicate a plan to obtain a monopoly
                    in South Manchuria of electric power.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
